				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-09-18T19:02:23.284289-05:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "Cv6W4337DQCZmGwSDqFdyA=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "The cool thing about these diagrams is that we all want the same things from it: no matter if you are an architect, an individual contributor, an auditor, or involved in due diligence, you want to see data flow, external surface area, network segmentation, data warehousing, et al. If we do things right, we can use the same diagrams (or maybe with slight redactions) for onboarding, Architecture Decision Records, threat modelling and other workshops, and DD and audits. Wouldn’t that be nice?"
			},
