				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-09-18T18:50:15.459892-05:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-09-18T18:52:00.025432-05:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "2Z1ywH37DQCzVBrbDqFdyA=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "Below is a quick list of my principles. If you do most of these, we can be friends (if you don’t, I’ll still be your friend, but I’ll judge you for your life choices)."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-09-18T18:52:01.874252-05:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-09-18T19:55:38.868945-05:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "9F7Kxn37DQC31qKwDqFdyA=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "- **Generate the data.** The diagram should rely on data, and the data should be autogenerated. Generate it during CI, export it from your cloud or hosting provider, do what you need to do to get to the truth.\n- **Make it text-first.** This makes the diagram diffable over time. You see what components were added, removed, changed, moved. It’s awesome.\n- **Timestamp it.** Embed some meta-information (commit hash, generation time, etc.) in the diagram.\n- **Regenerate it on change.** Whenever the architecture changes, the diagram has to change. Ideally after CI has run (I always love to see a `doc` stage in CI definitions).\n- **Use redactions to make it publishable.** If you want to share it somewhere, you can redact sensible information first (easy when you generate a bunch of data in a sensible format!). This way you can share it on external documentation or during DDs (thank you!).\n- **Multiple views over the model.** A model can encapsulate the whole system, but a view cannot. Give me multiple pictures (see below for a list of views)."
			},
